Notes: Phillip Rogers was born in 1949; from an early age he was a keen amateur photographer; as a young man he collaborated with his friend Martin Brennan to set up a folk/country music club called One-c-one, operating out of a disused community hall in back lane, North Carlton; he worked as a real estate agent and property investment advisor often photographing properties or developments he was involved with; he enjoyed the documentary aspect of photography - the urban landscape, the absurdities or ugliness of modern life, as well as it's beauty. This collection of his photographs Includes views of country Victorian social life, landscapes and urban scenes, captured on a Rollieflex SLR, printed by photographer.
